    • Field Detail

      • userList

        private static HashMap<String,​User> userList
        UserDB class to manage the user database. This class is responsible for adding, removing, and retrieving users from the database. It uses a HashMap to store users with their userId as the key.
        See Also:
        User

      • CSV_FILE_PATH

        private static final String CSV_FILE_PATH
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

    • Constructor Detail

      • UserDB

        public UserDB()
        Constructor to initialize the UserDB object with a user list. The user list is represented as a HashMap where the key is the userId and the value is the User object.

    • Method Detail

      • init

        public static void init()
        Method to initialize the user list. This method is called to reload the user list from the CSV file.

      • exportToCsv

        public static void exportToCsv()
        Method to export users to a CSV file. As a no-databse implementation, data persistency is achieved through exporting to CSV files. This method is only useful after the first run of the program.

      • readFromCsv

        public static void readFromCsv()
                        throws IOException
        Method to read users from a CSV file. This method is only useful after the first run of the program where the users are processed and exported before. If first-run, use processRawCsv(String, UserType) instead.
        Throws:
        IOException - If there is an error reading the CSV file.

      • processRawCsv

        public static void processRawCsv​(String filename,
                                 UserType userType)
        Method to process raw CSV files for different user types. This method reads the CSV file, creates User objects, and adds them to the user list.
        Parameters:
        filename - The name of the CSV file to be processed.
        userType - The type of user to be processed (Applicant, HDB Officer, or HDB Manager).

      • addUser

        public static void addUser​(User user)
        Method to add a user to the user list. The user is added to the HashMap with the userId as the key.
        Parameters:
        user - The User object to be added to the user list.

      • typecastUser

        public static User typecastUser​(User user)
        Helper function to typecast the user object to the correct type. Takes in a general User object and returns the specific type of user.
        Parameters:
        user - The User object to be typecasted.
        Returns:
        The specific type of user (Applicant, HDBOfficer, or HDBManager).

      • getUserById

        public static User getUserById​(String userId)
        Method to retrieve a user from the user list using the userId.
        Parameters:
        userId - The unique identifier of the user to be retrieved.
        Returns:
        The User object associated with the given userId, or null if not found.

      • getUserByName

        public static User getUserByName​(String name)
        Method to retrieve a user from the user list using their name.
        Parameters:
        name - The name of the user to be retrieved. (This program assumes that names are unique)
        Returns:
        The User object associated with the given name, or null if not found.

      • removeUser

        public static void removeUser​(String userId)
        Method to remove a user from the user list using the userId.
        Parameters:
        userId - The unique identifier of the user to be removed.

      • userExists

        public static boolean userExists​(String userId)
        Method to check if a user exists in the user list using the userId.
        Parameters:
        userId - The unique identifier of the user to be checked.
        Returns:
        true if the user exists, false otherwise.

      • getUserList

        public static HashMap<String,​User> getUserList()
        Method to get the user list.
        Returns:
        The HashMap containing all users in the user list.

      • clearUserList

        public static void clearUserList()
        Method to clear the user list. This method removes all users from the user list.

      • getUserCount

        public static int getUserCount()
        Method to get the count of users in the user list.
        Returns:
        The number of users in the user list.

      • isEmpty

        public static boolean isEmpty()
        Method to check if the user list is empty.
        Returns:
        true if the user list is empty, false otherwise.

      • printUserList

        public static void printUserList()
        Method to print the user list. This method prints all users in the user list to the console.

      • updateUser

        public static void updateUser​(User user)
        Method to update a user in the user list. This method replaces the existing user with the same userId with the new user object.
        Parameters:
        user - The User object to be updated in the user list.
